message:
Closes #1306 - review: Suppress findbugs warning BC_BAD_CAST_TO_ABSTRACT_COLLECTION.

Copied from https://github.com/mozilla-mobile/focus-android/pull/1555#issuecomment-339365588:

> https://public-artifacts.taskcluster.net/S_gwYP5cR2C0eVCnS06xZQ/0/public/findbugs/findbugs.html

The error is `BC_BAD_CAST_TO_ABSTRACT_COLLECTION`

>  Questionable cast from Collection to abstract class java.util.List  in org.mozilla.focus.utils.FileUtils$Companion.deleteContent(File, Set)

Looking at the decompiled bytecode from Kotlin:

```java
            Collection element$iv = (Collection)(new ArrayList());

            for(int it = 0; it < $receiver$iv$iv.length; ++it) {
               Object $i$a$1$all = $receiver$iv$iv[it];
               File $i$f$all = (File)$i$a$1$all;
               if(!doNotEraseWhitelist.contains($i$f$all.getName())) {
                  element$iv.add($i$a$1$all);
               }
            }

            List filesToDelete = (List)element$iv;
```

The corresponding kotlin code is:
```kotlin
val filesToDelete = directory.listFiles()?.filter { !doNotEraseWhitelist.contains(it.name) } ?: return false
return filesToDelete.all { it.deleteRecursively() }
```

So we're casting to `Collection` to filter but casting back to `List` to store
the temporary variable.

It looks like others have seen this problem: here's [an issue filed for
findbugs](https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/KT-18311) and [the issue it was
duped to](https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/KT-16446). Neither appears to be
verified by the core maintainers or prioritized (the original issue is filed in
Feb 2017).

I think the best course of action here is to suppress the error.

Switch to copyless String reversal

This should reduce memory allocations a little, and is a usefu;
step in switching the entirety of UrlMatcher to revhost based matching.
